  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of primary hyperaldosteronism (PH) within the last 3 years, either with or
             without an aldosterone producing adenoma (APA).

          -  Hypertension at screening

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Persistent hypokalemia

          -  Renal impairment

          -  Significant hepatic disease

          -  Any surgical or medical condition which may significantly alter the absorption,
             distribution, metabolism or excretion of any drug substance

        Other protocol-defined inclusion/exclusion criteria may apply
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
